that you mentioned before?

101
00:07:09,360 --> 00:07:10,360
Let me introduce.

102
00:07:10,860 --> 00:07:12,940
This is my classmate, Yang Kaizhi.

103
00:07:13,620 --> 00:07:15,210
This is Li Renjun.

104
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:17,120
This is Miss Yoshiko,

105
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:19,510
Drillmaster Hirata's fiancée.

106
00:07:24,340 --> 00:07:26,070
We have great respect

107
00:07:26,480 --> 00:07:27,920
for Captain Hirata.

108
00:07:27,940 --> 00:07:31,890
I wish him a safe return.

109
00:07:33,050 --> 00:07:34,490
Many thanks.

110
00:07:34,750 --> 00:07:36,920
Congratulations to you guys, too.

111
00:07:37,830 --> 00:07:38,560
Liang Xiang.

112
00:07:49,960 --> 00:07:51,750
You leaving us at this time

113
00:07:52,790 --> 00:07:54,430
really makes me sad.

114
00:07:55,430 --> 00:07:56,630
Any news from Hirata?

115
00:07:58,920 --> 00:07:59,630
Last night,

116
00:08:00,190 --> 00:08:02,900
the commander of the General Staff Headquarters
came to my house

117
00:08:02,900 --> 00:08:04,500
and told me something,

118
00:08:08,630 --> 00:08:10,480
which kept me awake all night.

119
00:08:10,600 --> 00:08:11,510
What did he say?

120
00:08:13,830 --> 00:08:16,070
He said that in just one battle last month,

121
00:08:16,070 --> 00:08:18,910
3,500 people were killed.

122
00:08:21,870 --> 00:08:22,830
Oh my god.

123
00:08:24,130 --> 00:08:24,730
What about

124
00:08:25,190 --> 00:08:26,390
Drillmaster Hirata?

125
00:08:34,270 --> 00:08:35,200
That's why I said

126
00:08:36,360 --> 00:08:38,440
you leaving at this moment

127
00:08:40,240 --> 00:08:42,510
makes me really sad.

128
00:08:59,570 --> 00:09:01,540
Come to my place

129
00:09:02,270 --> 00:09:03,170
after the banquet.

130
00:09:03,170 --> 00:09:04,720
I have something for you.

131
00:09:05,670 --> 00:09:06,200
Okay.

132
00:09:09,870 --> 00:09:11,400
Come on, let's have a toast!

133
00:09:11,440 --> 00:09:12,240
Okay. Come on!

134
00:09:12,320 --> 00:09:12,960
Cheers!

135
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:14,080
Come on. Cheers!

136
00:09:15,630 --> 00:09:16,510
Cheers!

137
00:09:21,200 --> 00:09:23,050
Hey, I heard from Renjun that

138
00:09:23,120 --> 00:09:23,910
you were planning to stay

139
00:09:23,910 --> 00:09:25,510
in Tokyo for a while longer. Is that true?

140
00:09:25,510 --> 00:09:26,000
Yeah.

141
00:09:26,420 --> 00:09:27,630
Why don't you leave with us?

142
00:09:27,630 --> 00:09:30,030
That way, we would come and leave together.

143
00:09:30,140 --> 00:09:32,000
We have to find a way out, don't we?

144
00:09:32,020 --> 00:09:33,350
How can I compare to you?

145
00:09:35,040 --> 00:09:37,510
Right. I'll go back and test
the waters first.

146
00:09:37,510 --> 00:09:38,550
If I have a way out,

147
00:09:38,790 --> 00:09:40,390
I'm sure you'll have one too.

148
00:09:40,630 --> 00:09:41,510
They have brought my mother

149
00:09:41,510 --> 00:09:42,970
from Jingzhou to Beijing,

150
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:43,870
to a house

151
00:09:43,870 --> 00:09:45,000
in Guangmingdian Alley.

152
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:47,080
It's also an old house of our ancestors.

153
00:09:47,080 --> 00:09:47,670
Kaizhi,

154
00:09:48,390 --> 00:09:49,850
just wait for my good news.

155
00:10:02,440 --> 00:10:02,870
Duke.

156
00:10:04,220 --> 00:10:05,280
What is this about?

157
00:10:05,870 --> 00:10:07,870
You're even packing them yourself.

158
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:10,200
These are all for you.

159
00:10:11,200 --> 00:10:11,960
I'll arrange for someone

160
00:10:11,960 --> 00:10:14,160
to ship them for you along with the boat.

161
00:10:15,850 --> 00:10:17,250
You're too kind.

162
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:21,840
Giving a man a fishing net

163
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:24,210
is better than giving him a fresh fish.

164
00:10:24,320 --> 00:10:25,650
This saying is not mine.

165
00:10:25,700 --> 00:10:27,460
Your ancestors said it.

166
00:10:34,600 --> 00:10:36,000
For the past three years,

167
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:36,870
Duke,

168
00:10:37,320 --> 00:10:40,160
you've been encouraging and
guiding me all the time.

169
00:10:40,160 --> 00:10:40,890
Liang Xiang.

170
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:42,400
Let me put it this way.

171
00:10:43,550 --> 00:10:44,360
Before you,

172
00:10:44,790 --> 00:10:45,510
there had never been

173
00:10:45,510 --> 00:10:47,170
a Qing Dynasty's royal family

174
00:10:47,200 --> 00:10:48,960
that was so close to

175
00:10:49,040 --> 00:10:50,570
our Japanese royal family.

176
00:10:51,240 --> 00:10:51,870
Actually,

177
00:10:52,270 --> 00:10:53,080
our two countries

178
00:10:53,080 --> 00:10:55,200
have had very similar experiences.

179
00:10:55,720 --> 00:10:58,320
It's just that Japan took a step
forward first.

180
00:10:58,750 --> 00:11:00,320
And I have the responsibility

181
00:11:00,320 --> 00:11:01,790
to convey our experiences

182
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:03,150
to you.

183
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:06,630
In the past year or two,

184
00:11:07,080 --> 00:11:08,320
your officials

185
00:11:08,320 --> 00:11:10,120
have frequently visited Japan,

186
00:11:10,750 --> 00:11:12,080
trying to learn from us.

187
00:11:12,790 --> 00:11:14,960
But what can you really see

188
00:11:15,080 --> 00:11:16,540
with such cursory visits?

189
00:11:18,440 --> 00:11:19,700
It's nothing more than

190
00:11:19,870 --> 00:11:21,320
the Emperor eating beef,

191
00:11:21,870 --> 00:11:23,870
officials wearing tailcoats,

192
00:11:24,390 --> 00:11:27,190
and the whole country embracing
Western customs:

193
00:11:27,270 --> 00:11:31,000
eating Western food, wearing Western clothes,
speaking English,

194
00:11:31,630 --> 00:11:32,760
parting their hair,

195
00:11:33,200 --> 00:11:34,260
dancing ballroom,

196
00:11:34,670 --> 00:11:35,930
marrying Westerners,

197
00:11:37,080 --> 00:11:39,390
Western suits and Japanese Kimonos coexisting,

198
00:11:39,390 --> 00:11:41,270
bars and tea houses coexisting,

199
00:11:42,270 --> 00:11:43,270
and Western operas

200
00:11:43,270 --> 00:11:45,930
and Japanese Ukiyo-e competing
for attention.

201
00:11:47,080 --> 00:11:47,960
No, no, no.

202
00:11:49,120 --> 00:11:51,980
None of them are the fundamentals
of today's Japan.

203
00:11:52,790 --> 00:11:53,750
In comparison,

204
00:11:54,510 --> 00:11:55,600
you know us

205
00:11:55,600 --> 00:11:56,960
better than they do.

206
00:11:58,010 --> 00:11:59,450
We've lived together

207
00:11:59,480 --> 00:12:00,810
for almost three years.

208
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:01,840
Right.

209
00:12:03,030 --> 00:12:05,080
If a person does not have the opportunity

210
00:12:05,080 --> 00:12:06,720
to view their

211
00:12:06,760 --> 00:12:07,630
ever-thriving country,

212
00:12:07,630 --> 00:12:09,320
land, and civilization

213
00:12:09,480 --> 00:12:11,210
from beyond national borders,

214
00:12:12,510 --> 00:12:14,790
then they will never be able

215
00:12:14,910 --> 00:12:16,840
to have a more precise perspective

216
00:12:16,840 --> 00:12:19,150
on the world and life.

217
00:12:23,720 --> 00:12:24,510
You want me

218
00:12:24,960 --> 00:12:26,890
to see my own country in a new light?

219
00:12:28,720 --> 00:12:30,270
You really understood me.

220
00:12:30,600 --> 00:12:32,150
You want me to see the crux of
my country's problems,

221
00:12:32,150 --> 00:12:32,630
and then

222
00:12:33,080 --> 00:12:33,940
revitalize it.

223
00:12:38,720 --> 00:12:40,000
For a young man

224
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:41,200
with a second lieutenant rank,

225
00:12:41,200 --> 00:12:42,870
isn't this a bit too grand?

226
00:12:44,390 --> 00:12:45,670
What you're bringing back to China

227
00:12:45,670 --> 00:12:47,150
is not just a diploma,

228
00:12:48,030 --> 00:12:49,030
but also this.

229
00:12:50,630 --> 00:12:53,960
In the future, if China falls into chaos,

230
00:12:54,390 --> 00:12:55,440
I hope you can

231
00:12:55,720 --> 00:12:56,860
remember Japan's nurturing

232
00:12:56,860 --> 00:12:59,110
of you today.

233
00:13:06,320 --> 00:13:07,600
Can you take a detour

234
00:13:07,620 --> 00:13:10,190
from that street on the left?

235
00:13:10,870 --> 00:13:12,050
You mean this street?

236
00:13:12,050 --> 00:13:12,930
Yes.

237
00:13:13,390 --> 00:13:14,030
No need to stop.

238
00:13:14,030 --> 00:13:16,090
Let's just have a little ride around.

239
00:13:22,690 --> 00:13:24,450
Sausages, 110 catties.

240
00:13:29,770 --> 00:13:30,980
Beef jerky,

241
00:13:37,010 --> 00:13:38,050
114 catties.

242
00:13:52,720 --> 00:13:55,270
Stop the carriage. Pull over.

243
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:24,160
Let's go! Quick!

244
00:14:24,950 --> 00:14:26,760
Get lost, you bastard!

245
00:14:28,120 --> 00:14:28,690
Go away!

246
00:14:35,310 --> 00:14:37,550
Get lost!

247
00:14:43,390 --> 00:14:44,030
Get lost!

248
00:14:44,330 --> 00:14:45,030
Bastard!

